{
  "stem": "7832.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then-- then as we were coming down almost to the end of the road, I looked on the side of the road, and there was my mother and the children.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were going on the truck.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, oh good, they don't have to walk.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It'll be so good for them to go on the-- you know, they're taking-- oh, how nice, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I thought it was so great that they were getting on a truck.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[CRYING] And then we never saw them again.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then we found out where those trucks were going.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I was-- I was a little bit at peace, knowing that they were a little bit better taken care of.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then us-- they took us maybe-- well, we got to this big hall.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It looked like such a humongous place, but we were pushed together, like in like half of the room.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But then I realized that there was very few of us there, compared to what came on the train.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I mean, almost a half a ghetto was on the train, and there was just one room full of us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And-- but I didn't have time to speculate or look around for anything, because they ordered us to take off our clothes.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a row of gestapo on one side of the room, and then there was a-- a row of benches that was separating us from them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they were standing with big German shepherd, about this big.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I have never seen such a big dog in my whole life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They were holding them real close by there-- you know, on a-- on a collar.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they were telling us to take our clothes off, so we all took our clothes off, and-- up to the underwear.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
